    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine sancte et individue trinitatis.<persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/32"> Karolus </persName>divina favente clementia<rs
                            key="#Emperor/king"> imperator </rs>augustus. Si petitionibus fidelium
                        nostrorum maxime eorum, qui nostro fideliter parent imperio, aures
                        celsitudinis nostre accomodamus, non solum imperialem in hoc exercemus
                        dignitatem, verum etiam eterne retributionis premia inde nobis largiri
                        procul dubio credimus. Quapropter cognoscat omnium fidelium nostrorum
                        presentium videlicet et futurorum industria, <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Bishops" ref="#people/33">Liutuuardum
                        </persName>venerabilem <rs key="#Bishops">episcopum</rs> et dilectum <rs
                            key="#Archchancellor">archicanzellarium</rs> nostram postulasse
                        serenitatem, ut sanctissimo <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/81"
                            key="#Plebs #Districtio #Baptismal_churches #Bishops">patri
                            Eusebio</orgName> defensori christiane fidei aliqua de iure regni nostri
                        concederemus et aliqua que subtracta sunt redderemus. Statimque nos
                        postulationes illius saluberrimas agnoscentes decrevimus ita fieri.
                        Concessimus itaque prefato sancto Eusebio cortem nostram magnam que dicitur
                            <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Tolls #Teloneum #Districtio"
                            ref="#estates/60"><placeName ref="#places/102"
                                key="#Curtes #Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Tolls #Teloneum #Districtio"
                                >Regio </placeName></geogName>antiquo nuncupatur vulgo cum tota<rs
                            key="#Forests"> silva </rs>eiusdem et <placeName ref="#places/49"
                            key="#Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Tolls #Teloneum #Districtio"
                            >fulgitio</placeName> et cum omnibus cortibus et villis, cum <placeName
                            key="#Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Tolls #Teloneum #Districtio"
                            ref="#places/103">valle Cliui</placeName> et omnibus eorum pertinentiis
                        simul cum corte de <geogName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Curtes #Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Tolls #Teloneum #Districtio"
                            ref="#estates/99"><placeName
                                key="#Uncertain_tradition #Curtes #Forests #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Tolls"
                                ref="#places/3728">Roueredo</placeName></geogName> cum omnibus suis
                        adiacentiis, dedimus etiam <rs key="#Curtes">cortem </rs>nostram magnam que
                        dicitur <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Tolls #Teloneum #Districtio"
                            ref="#estates/62"><placeName ref="#places/50" key="#Curtes">Bugella
                            </placeName></geogName>cum omnibus cortibus et villis alpibus et omnibus
                        suis pertinentiis, contulimus et reddidimus cortem <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Tolls #Teloneum #Districtio"
                            ref="#estates/63"><placeName ref="#places/51"
                                key="#Curtes #Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Tolls #Teloneum #Districtio"
                                >Sestinium</placeName></geogName> cum omnibus alpibus et
                        pertinentiis suis, ut muris sanctis in censuali calce perpetuo deserviret,
                        donavimus et restituimus cortem <geogName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Curtes #Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Tolls #Teloneum #Districtio"
                            ref="#estates/88"><placeName ref="#places/532"
                                key="#Uncertain_tradition #Curtes #Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Tolls #Teloneum #Districtio"
                                >Romanianum</placeName></geogName> cum omnibus suis vallibus alpibus
                        et suis pertinentiis, et confirmavimus totam <rs key="#Forests">silvam
                            </rs><placeName key="#Forests" ref="#places/96">Rouasindam
                        </placeName>pertinentem ad <rs key="#Plebs #Baptismal_churches">plebem
                            </rs><orgName key="#Plebs #Baptismal_churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/83">sancti Laurentii</orgName> ipsius
                        Vercellensis ecclesie, reddidimus et confirmavimus<rs
                            key="#Bridges/pontoons"> pontem </rs><placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Bridges/pontoons" ref="#places/104"
                            >Notingum</placeName>, quem<persName key="#Bishops" ref="#people/109">
                            Notingus</persName> episcopus eiusdem <placeName ref="#places/106"
                            key="#Bishops">Vercellensis</placeName> ecclesie mirabiliter super eum
                        equitando per legem recepit, dedimus cortem <geogName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Curtes #Fiscal_property #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Tolls #Teloneum #Districtio"
                            ref="#estates/89"><placeName ref="#places/107"
                                key="#Uncertain_tradition #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Trecade</placeName>
                        </geogName>cum omnibus suis pertinentiis, dedimus <geogName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Tolls #Teloneum #Districtio"
                            ref="#estates/96">cortem iuris nostri <placeName
                                key="#Uncertain_tradition #Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Tolls #Teloneum #Districtio"
                                ref="#places/99">Firminianam</placeName></geogName> cum omnibus suis
                        pertinentiis, obtulimus et restituimus cortem <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Tolls #Teloneum #Districtio"
                            ref="#estates/41"><placeName ref="#places/3"
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Tolls #Teloneum #Districtio"
                                >Carixianam </placeName></geogName>cum <placeName ref="#places/100"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object">Langusco</placeName> sibi adiacente et
                        cum omnibus suis pertinentiis, largiti sumus et reddidimus cortes de
                            <geogName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Tolls #Teloneum #Districtio"
                            ref="#estates/97"><placeName ref="#places/101"
                                key="#Uncertain_tradition #Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Tolls #Teloneum #Districtio"
                                >Pasiliano</placeName></geogName> et <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Tolls #Teloneum #Districtio"
                            ref="#estates/98"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Tolls #Teloneum #Districtio"
                                ref="#places/105">Occimiano</placeName></geogName> cum omnibus suis
                        pertinentiis. Hec omnia sancta Vercellensis ecclesia proprio iure in eternum
                        habeat cum omnibus publicis <rs key="#Districtio">districtis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Tolls #Teloneum"> teloneum </rs><rs key="#Fisheries"
                            >piscationibus</rs> venationibus <rs key="#Ports">portibus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Mills">molendinis</rs> montibus et vallibus alpibus <rs
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">edificiis</rs> mancipiis utriusque
                        sexus agris vineis capellis pratis pascuis <rs key="#Forests">silvis</rs><rs
                            key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters"> aquis aquarumque
                            decursibus cultis et incultis </rs>et de nostro iure et dominio in ius
                        et dominium prelibate ecclesie tradimus atque transfundimus. Si quis autem
                        hanc nostram traditionem infringere temptaverit, eiusdem piissimi Eusebii
                        iram incurrat, insuper rectoribus ecclesie persolvendum centum libras auri
                        purissimi culpabilis habeatur. Et ut hec traditio pleniorem in dei nomine
                        obtineat firmitatem, hoc nostre auctoritatis preceptum fieri mandavimus
                        propriaque manu confirmantes anulo nostro iussimus sigillari. Signum (M.)
                        domni Karoli serenissimi imperatoris augusti. </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
